# Networking Core Protocols

**Room:** [TryHackMe – Networking Core Protocols](https://tryhackme.com/room/networkingcoreprotocols)
**Status:** Completed

## Summary
Practiced analyzing cleartext application-layer protocols (FTP, SMTP,
POP3, IMAP) using both Wireshark traffic inspection and the command-line
FTP client to retrieve files from a live target.

## Key Commands
\`\`\`bash
ftp <target-ip>          # Connect to FTP server
ls                        # List remote directory
get flag.txt              # Retrieve file from server
cat flag.txt               # Read file contents locally
\`\`\`

## Wireshark Analysis
- Used **Follow TCP Stream** to reconstruct an entire FTP session
  (USER/PASS authentication, PASV mode, RETR file transfer, QUIT)
- Observed how FTP transmits credentials and commands in plaintext —
  a key reason it's considered insecure for production use.
